{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1782584391, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "OpenTrajectory — the wedge"}
[0.01977, "o", "\u001b[1mOpenTrajectory — the wedge in one terminal\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2mlive agent run  →  one portable file  →  the Inspector tells you *why* it failed\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[1.224322, "o", "\u001b[0;36m# 0. Build the zero-dep capture SDK (Node built-ins only — corp-airlock safe)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.929593, "o", "\u001b[1m$ cd packages/capture && npm run build && cd ../..\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.121867, "o", "   built dist/\r\n\r\n"]
[5.025005, "o", "\u001b[0;36m# 1. Capture a Claude Code session transcript -> the open OpenTrajectory format\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.728168, "o", "\u001b[1m$ ot capture demo/wedge-session.jsonl -o run.ot.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.384713, "o", "[claude-code] wrote 4 steps -> /tmp/tmp.wjzsOCyCoP/run.ot.json (status: failure)\r\n"]
[6.399473, "o", "\r\n"]
[7.302063, "o", "\u001b[0;36m#    one self-contained JSON file — ordered steps, tool calls, an outcome. Peek at it:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.007482, "o", "\u001b[1m$ jq '{harness:.harness.name, model, status:.outcome.status, steps:(.steps|length)}' run.ot.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.521773, "o", "\u001b[1;39m{\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;34m\"harness\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"claude-code\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;34m\"model\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"claude-opus-4-8\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;34m\"status\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"failure\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;34m\"steps\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m4\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;39m}\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.523031, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.429789, "o", "\u001b[0;36m# 2. It's conformant to the spec (§7) — gate this in any CI with the same check\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.133214, "o", "\u001b[1m$ ot validate run.ot.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.765755, "o", "✓ doc[0] conformant\r\n"]
[10.772018, "o", "\r\n"]
[11.674146, "o", "\u001b[0;36m# 3. Audit it. ot diagnose is the in-terminal twin of the Inspector's heuristic —\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.377415, "o", "\u001b[0;36m#    same signal, no browser, no API key:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.080355, "o", "\u001b[1m$ ot diagnose run.ot.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.683645, "o", "   HARNESS (Context Gap) · conf 0.65\r\n     - missing-context marker: ImportError while importing test module 'tests/test_auth.py'.\r\n"]
[13.690688, "o", "\r\n"]
[14.592799, "o", "\u001b[0;32m\u001b[1m   ↑ not just 'it failed' — *why*: the env withheld a dependency (HARNESS), not a model gap.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[15.996266, "o", "\u001b[0;36m# Why that distinction is the whole game — same task, three turns, three different reasons:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[17.304454, "o", "\u001b[1m$ bash demo/loop/run.sh\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[17.818766, "o", "TASK (fixed across all turns): make the auth test suite pass\r\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\r\n\r\n── Turn: the run can't even start\r\n"]
[17.823051, "o", "$ ot diagnose 1-harness.ot.json\r\n"]
[17.967254, "o", "   HARNESS (Context Gap) · conf 0.8\r\n"]
[17.967677, "o", "     - missing-context marker: ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'jwt'\r\n     - missing-context marker: the package index is unreachable in this sandbox\r\n"]
[17.976043, "o", "   → fix the lever the diagnosis named: HARNESS → fix the ENVIRONMENT (provision the 'jwt' dependency), not the model.\r\n\r\n── Turn: now it runs, but the fix is wrong\r\n"]
[17.979972, "o", "$ ot diagnose 2-product.ot.json\r\n"]
[18.229999, "o", "   PRODUCT (Unclassified Failure) · conf 0.3\r\n"]
[18.239484, "o", "   → fix the lever the diagnosis named: PRODUCT → a model CAPABILITY gap. Give it the missing context (point it at the refresh path).\r\n\r\n"]
[18.239574, "o", "── Turn: resolved\r\n"]
[18.245146, "o", "$ ot diagnose 3-clean.ot.json\r\n"]
[18.367109, "o", "   CLEAN (Clean) · conf 0.9\r\n"]
[18.371747, "o", "   → fix the lever the diagnosis named: none — CLEAN. The loop converged.\r\n\r\n"]
[18.371843, "o", "═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\r\nConvergence:  HARNESS → PRODUCT → CLEAN\r\nLevers pulled: fix the harness → improve the model's context → done\r\n\r\n"]
[18.37216, "o", "The point: each turn failed for a DIFFERENT reason. A pass/fail score can't\r\n"]
[18.37231, "o", "tell them apart — so it can't tell you what to change. The DIAGNOSIS can, and\r\nthat's the steering signal a self-improvement loop runs on. Mis-attribute turn 1\r\nas a model problem and you burn a fine-tuning run on a missing 'pip install'.\r\n"]
[18.373582, "o", "\r\n"]
[19.276422, "o", "\u001b[1mThat's the wedge.\u001b[0m Every harness already records this spine; OpenTrajectory is the\r\none portable file they can all emit, and the Inspector is the validated reader that\r\n"]
[19.27725, "o", "already exists. Open, cross-harness, eval-first — \u001b[2mnot\u001b[0m the retraining loop.\r\n\r\n\u001b[2mDrop the same run.ot.json into inspector/index.html (\"▲ Inspect yours\") for the\r\nfull visual audit + the LLM-judge column. Headless proof: node inspector/test-ingest.mjs\u001b[0m\r\n"]
